 :tx/rationale "Create task: COTX-1: Harvest-session cotransaction — atomic session rotation in harvest commit. BACKGROUND: The causal prerequisite for all other cotransactions. Currently harvest writes harvest metadata but does NOT close the active session. The next command's detect_session_start checks for active sessions but can't create a new one if the old one isn't closed. This caused a stale session to persist for 10+ sessions (Session 021→031). FIX: Harvest --commit atomically closes the old session and opens a new one in the SAME transaction. Zero-width session boundary. APPROACH: In harvest.rs run(), after building all_datoms and before writing TxFile: (1) Query active session entity — use same pattern as query_session_start_fitness in status.rs. Scan :session/started-at for entities with :session/status = :session.status/active and no later closed assertion. (2) If active session exists: append session-close datoms to all_datoms — Datom(session_entity, :session/status, :session.status/closed, harvest_tx_id, Assert). (3) Generate new session entity: ident = :session/s-{harvest_tx_wall_time}. (4) Compute start-fitness via compute_fitness(&store) (already called earlier in the function). (5) Append 7 datoms for new session: :db/ident, :session/started-at (harvest_tx wall_time as Long), :session/start-time (ISO 8601 String), :session/start-fitness (Double — current F(S)), :session/start-datom-count (Long — store.len() + all_datoms.len()), :session/status (:session.status/active), :session/current (self-ref). (6) The existing layout.write_tx(&tx_file) commits everything atomically. CRITICAL: The new session's start-datom-count must include the harvest datoms (they're in the same tx), so compute as store.len() + all_datoms.len(). EDGE CASES: (a) No active session (first harvest on fresh store) — skip close, just create new session. (b) Multiple active sessions (shouldn't happen, but handle gracefully) — close all, create one new. (c) harvest without --commit — no session rotation (dry run). WHAT CHANGES: detect_session_start in main.rs still fires on cold start (no prior harvest). But the hot path (work → harvest → work) uses harvest rotation. Session dashboard (META-7) becomes exact because session boundary = harvest boundary. ACCEPTANCE: (A) After harvest --commit, old session has status=closed. (B) After harvest --commit, new session has status=active with start-fitness and start-datom-count. (C) Old session close and new session open are in the SAME transaction (verify same tx_id). (D) Next braid command after harvest shows session progress from the new session baseline. (E) No regression: harvest without --commit does NOT rotate sessions. (F) detect_session_start still works for cold start (fresh store). DEPENDS-ON: EPIC t-b1ab00b6. FILE: crates/braid/src/commands/harvest.rs. TRACES TO: INV-HARVEST-007, INV-BILATERAL-001, INV-STORE-014."
